<h2><span>1.</span> Bariatric Surgery</h2>

<p>Bariatric Surgery refers to a series of weight loss procedures that an obese individual can have in order to reduce their food intake, therefore causing them to lose weight. A person is classed as obese if their Body Mass Index (BMI) is over 30. If their BMI is over 40, they are deemed severely obese.</p>
<a class="btn btn-link" href="http://www.drvikramlotwala.com/services/bariatric-surgery">Read More</a></div>

<div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 px-4 py-5 r-border">
<h2><span>2.</span> Laparoscopic Surgery</h2>

<p>Laparoscopic or &quot;Minimally Invasive&quot; Surgery is a specialized technique for performing surgery. In the past, this technique was commonly used for gynecologic surgery and for gall bladder surgery. Over the last 10 years the use of this technique has expanded into intestinal surgery.</p>
<a class="btn btn-link" href="http://www.drvikramlotwala.com/services/laparoscopic-surgery">Read More</a></div>

<div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-4 px-4 py-5">
<h2><span>3.</span> Diet &amp; Nutiriton</h2>

<p>We are here for Obesity, Hypertension, Diabetes Mellitus, PCOD (Polycystic Ovary Disease), Hypothyroidism, Underweight, Body Building through Diet Prescription and Lifestyle Management, Gynecology: Pregnancy &amp; Lactation, Gout, Cancer, Diet for Teenagers, Hyperlipidemia.</p>
<a class="btn btn-link" href="http://www.drvikramlotwala.com/services/diet-and-nutrition">Read More</a></div>
</div>
